Delta-v budget: dv = 2850 :m/s

    ~~~
    Total velocity change required for the mission trajectory.

    The Tsiolkovsky rocket equation relates $\Delta v$ to propellant mass:

    $$\Delta v = v_e \ln\!\frac{m_{wet}}{m_{dry}}$$

    Rearranging for required propellant:

    $$m_{req} = m_{dry}\left(e^{\Delta v / v_e} - 1\right)$$

    Higher $\Delta v$ exponentially increases required propellant — hence the
    sensitivity of mission design to trajectory choice.
    ~~~
